  "prompt": "What are some AngularJS interview questions?",
  "response": "Here are some common AngularJS interview questions that may be asked during an interview:\n\n1. What is AngularJS, and why is it popular?  \n2. What are the key features of AngularJS?  \n3. What is the difference between AngularJS and Angular (2+)?  \n4. Explain the concept of two-way data binding in AngularJS.  \n5. What is a directive in AngularJS? Can you provide examples of some built-in directives?  \n6. What are controllers in AngularJS, and how do they work?  \n7. What is a service in AngularJS? Name some built-in services.  \n8. What is a factory in AngularJS, and how is it different from a service?  \n9. What is dependency injection in AngularJS?  \n10. Explain the role of $scope in AngularJS.  \n11. What is the difference between $scope and $rootScope?  \n12. How does routing work in AngularJS?  \n13. What is the purpose of the `ng-app` directive?  \n14. What is the difference between `ng-if` and `ng-show/ng-hide`?  \n15. How do you create a custom directive in AngularJS?  \n16. What is a filter in AngularJS? Give examples of some built-in filters.  \n17. How do you handle form validation in AngularJS?  \n18. What is a promise in AngularJS, and how is it used?  \n19. Explain the concept of digest cycle in AngularJS.  \n20. How do you make an HTTP request in AngularJS?  \n\nThese questions cover a broad range of AngularJS concepts, from basic to advanced, and can help assess a candidate's understanding of the framework.",
